				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				If you think bards are terrible soloers, you should go to Misty Thicket and solo goblins and such until you get level 10. Then you should head to Steamfont Mountains and solo at the undead ruins. I went from lvl 1 to lvl 13 in one day. Then at 13 i headed to oasis of marr to take on caimans. At 15, i went to Highpass Hold and got to 17. Im at lvl 17 currently and am duel wielding either a blade of fiery lamentation and a PGT or a blade of FM and a bloodstained fang(depending on when the PGT procs). Im considering going to either Lake Rathetear or East Karana. Any hints would help, also at level 12 you can effectively solo with the bellow, but i suggest just straight up meleeing(faster exp IMHO). <BR>
