				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				as a bard, you are a support character, you buff, haste, regen, sow, mes, charm, fear,clarity, snare, slow mobs, etc etc, your role in the group is to find out what the group needs, (quickly) and adjust yourself, and your songs to best help the group, i see so many bards try to tank, and its not what bards are for, we have some great songs as well, right now at lvl 46, the lvl 1 chant of battle adds near 30 to str, agi and dex, group haste of 20% with an extra 23 agi (celerity lvl 36 song) and regen or clarity, and your rocking.<BR>
<BR>
bards save clerics alot of mana by slowing mobs, and throwing regen the group,<BR>
<BR>
bards make a group more effiecent.<BR>
<BR>
and bards can solo quite well, charm kiting is quit simple as a bard,<BR>
<BR>
i would agree with the above post, lvl 8 is hardly a lvl to judge a class, <BR>
